			<title>Explanation: Changing Energies</title>
			<statement>
				<p></p>
			  <p>Suppose you have a system that initially includes some kinetic energy and some potential energy.  You observe that the potential energy decreases by <m>7000 \mathrm{~J}</m> and the kinetic energy increases by <m>4500 \mathrm{~J}</m>.  Is the net external work on this system positive, negative, or zero?  Explain your reasoning.</p>
				</statement>
